# Statistical downscaling of MODIS Land Surface Temperature with Machine Learning

In this workshop we build a workflow to estimate high-resolution land surface temperature using satellite predictors and terrain information.

Coarse LST products (e.g. MODIS) capture large-scale temperature patterns but miss local variation. Higher-resolution optical and terrain data contain information about land cover, moisture, elevation, and urban structure, which all influence surface temperature.

The objective is to learn the relationship between LST and environmental predictors at coarse scale, and then apply that relationship to predict LST at finer resolution.

