## Phase 2: Train a ML model to predict LST at native MODIS resolution.

We create a relationship between variables that we know influence urban heat (such as the proportion of vegetation, water or built-up land) with land surface temperature at MODIS native resolution (1000m).

First, we load in the three data sources we need:

1.  MODIS: a land surface temperature from 12:55 on 17/7 2025
2.  A Sentinel-2 multispectral image composite from the month of July
3.  A digital surface model (DSM), describing the terrain and heights of buildings

The second two datasources have a naturally much higher resolution, but we resample it to the same resolution as the MODIS image so that we can analyze their relationship with our target variable (temperature).

```{python}
